{"lemma":"حِكايَةٌ","slug":"حِكايَةٌ","root":"ح.ك.#","root_slug":"ح-ك-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ك-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8733"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَكَى (ḥakā) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"story, tale"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"direct speech"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħi.kaː.ja/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8733","headword_ar":"حِكَايَةٌ","root":"HkY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of 1. (S, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  [Used as a simple subst., it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A narrative, story,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tale:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HakaAyaAtN","text_ar":"حَكَايَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  As a conventional term in grammar, [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Imitation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conforming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in language,] it is of two kinds:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HikaAyapu jumolapK","text_ar":"حِكَايَةُ جُمْلَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The imitation of a proposition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"phrase"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HikaAyapu muforadK","text_ar":"حِكَايَةُ مُفْرَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The imitation of a single word"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the former is of two sorts; one of which is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HikaAyapu malofuwZK","text_ar":"حِكَايَةُ مَلْفُوظٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The imitation of a thing uttered"},{"kind":"text","text":"], whereof"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAluwA AlHamodu ll~`hi","text_ar":"قَالُوا الحَمْدُ للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[They said, “ Praise be to God, ” (Kur vii. 41,)] is an ex.; and the other,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HikaAyapu makotuwbK","text_ar":"حِكَايَةُ مَكْتُوبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The imitation of a thing written"},{"kind":"text","text":"], whereof"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraA^otu EalaY faS~ihi muHam~adN","text_ar":"قَرَاْتُ عَلَى فَصِّهِ مُحَمَّدٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasuwlu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"رَسُولُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[I read upon his ring-stone, “ Mohammad is the Apostle of God, ”] is an ex.: and the latter kind, also, (that of a single word,) is of two sorts; one of which is with the interrogative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~N","text_ar":"اَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano","text_ar":"مَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as when, to one who says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulFA","text_ar":"رَجُلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulaA","text_ar":"رَجُلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", I saw a man], you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay~aA","text_ar":"اَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[What (man)?], or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaA","text_ar":"مَنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[Whom?], and the like, which sort is agreeable with a common rule; the other sort being without an interrogative, as the saying of one of the Arabs, to one who said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAtaAni tamorataAni","text_ar":"هَاتَانِ تَمْرَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[These are two dates],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEonaA mino tamorataAni","text_ar":"دَعْنَا مِنْ تَمْرَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[Abstain thou from troubling us about two dates], which sort is anomalous. (El-Ashmoonee's Expos. of the Alfeeyeh of Ibn-Málik.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HikaAyapu SawotK","text_ar":"حِكَايَةُ صَوْتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A word imitative of a sound; an onomatopœia:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisomu SawotK","text_ar":"اِسْمُ صَوْتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smw","text_ar":"سمو"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}